1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Taking walks and playing games when there's sunny weather

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:15,000
If there's rain, they're singing songs or reading books together

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Every day just has a way of feeling extra lucky

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:26,000
When you spend it with a friend, just like Bjorn and Bucky

5
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Just like Bjorn and Bucky!

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:49,000
I think it's the highest a kite's ever flown ever!

7
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Gosh, it's pretty! Can I have a turn?

8
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Of course, just be sure you hold it real tight

9
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Yeah, sure!

10
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Why is it falling?

11
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:01,000
The wind died down

12
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Look out for that tree!

13
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Well, that's that

14
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Not on my watch!

15
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,000
I'll get it down!

16
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Ha-ha!

17
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Oh, Bucky?

18
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
You might want to back up!

19
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Ha-ha!

20
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:21,000
The bear!

21
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Touch the sky!

22
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Nope!

23
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,000
That was the sky's fault!

24
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Listen, you have to take your time

25
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,000
Climb slow and steady

26
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Plan each step

27
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:37,500
This time I'll get it!

28
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,960
I got it! I got it! I got it! I don't!

29
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:45,560
I'll get it! I'll get it! I'll get it! Come on!

30
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:48,760
Getting there...

31
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:50,600
Oh, no, you don't!

32
00:01:52,740 --> 00:01:56,600
Hey, guys, why don't we just leave that one there and make a new one?

33
00:01:56,740 --> 00:01:59,680
No way! Our kite doesn't belong to this tree!

34
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:02,080
Look, Bjorn's almost got it already!

35
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:05,920
Hey, Bjorn! No kite ever gets left behind!

36
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:09,080
I didn't get it down.

37
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:13,000
All right, we need better equipment.

38
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:21,140
Tree beat ladder. I'm going up to get our kite back.

39
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:23,260
Maybe hold the ladder.

40
00:02:25,340 --> 00:02:29,520
Bjorn, I can't quite reach it. I need backup.

41
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:30,640
Get up here!

42
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:35,920
Uh-huh. I can almost reach it!

43
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:38,200
Ugh! Franny, come up here!

44
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:42,380
We're so close!

45
00:02:42,540 --> 00:02:45,280
Just a teeny bit more. One strand of tail fur!

46
00:02:46,060 --> 00:02:48,420
Just be sure that you hold the ladder steady.

47
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:49,460
Don't let go!

48
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:54,300
Hey, Bucky. I was just wondering if all of us are up here, then who's...

49
00:02:54,300 --> 00:03:09,180
I think that I know what our best plan is now.

50
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:10,680
We just build a new kite?

51
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:11,080
What?

52
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:11,620
No.

53
00:03:11,860 --> 00:03:13,940
Now we make a tornado with our lungs.

54
00:03:14,580 --> 00:03:15,960
Blow as hard as you can.

55
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:24,160
Come on!

56
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:36,220
Oh, you've got to be kidding me!

57
00:03:50,220 --> 00:03:53,100
All right, guys, maybe we should stop.

58
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:53,780
You're right.

59
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:58,560
Throwing sticks is not smart because we might hurt the kite, but I've got the answer.

60
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:09,960
Friends, I give you the brand-newest incredible awesome invention.

61
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:11,600
It's the poultry poult.

62
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:12,660
Hop in, bud.

63
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:14,040
It's super simple to operate.

64
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,840
All you do is pull the lever.

65
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:19,620
Good test.

66
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:20,620
Good test.

67
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:23,620
This time we just aim a little better and try again.

68
00:04:23,620 --> 00:04:24,400
Try again.

69
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:28,400
And again.

70
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:30,400
And again.

71
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:33,400
And again.

72
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:42,400
So we might have exceeded operational capacity.

73
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,240
The poultry poult is kaput.

74
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:49,180
You guys, hey, why don't we make an even better kite instead?

75
00:04:49,180 --> 00:04:51,880
Hey, that sounds like a great idea.

76
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:53,720
Why didn't I think of that?

77
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,180
Franny, you're a genius.

78
00:04:55,180 --> 00:05:04,960
It's so pretty.

79
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:07,700
Can I have a turn?

80
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:08,700
Of course.

81
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:09,700
Here it is.

82
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:13,480
Just try not to let the wind do that again.

83
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,480
Oh, no.

84
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,480
Oh.

85
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:17,480
I don't like that tree.

86
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:19,880
So, we just build a new one, right?

87
00:05:19,880 --> 00:05:20,880
You kidding?

88
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,180
I can get it down.

89
00:05:22,180 --> 00:05:23,180
Ha ha!

90
00:05:23,180 --> 00:05:24,880
Here we go again.

